      "repair_reason": "- [P1] Human handling remains because the code cleanup is narrow but merge also depends on latest-head live Zen-only proof that automation cannot provide.; Needs attention: The functional provider changes do not show a credential leak, but the PR still includes a temporary CI artifact-packaging job that should be removed before merge.; Review finding: [P2] Allow negative Zen balances in the menu bar — Sources/CodexB... (sha=afd1fd7e9def7cc736a386a8a51fd36a6c8f0142)",
      "review_summary": "This PR adds OpenCode Go Zen balance-only fallback through workspace and billing fetches, balance-only snapshots, menu-card/status-item display paths, focused parser/fetcher/menu tests, plus a temporary PR artifact workflow and changelog entry.\n\nReproducibility: yes. The current-head source shows the billing parser accepts negative balances while the new menu-bar formatter rejects cost.used < 0, and the live discussion already reproduced the Zen-only card/menu-bar path on earlier artifacts.",
